<p>Following is an example code, it seems that intellisense doesn't recognize the <code>'exposedMethod'</code> when the class <code>'First'</code> is referenced in class <code>'Second'</code>.</p>  <p>Is this not supported by Intellisense or am I missing something?</p>  <pre><code>class First{     exposedMethod=()=&gt;{      } }  class Second{     firstClass;     constructor(firstClass:First)     {         firstClass = firstClass;     }      someFunction=()=&gt;{         this.firstClass.exposedMethod();    //No intellisense support here     } } </code></pre>